data.title: Meet Our Doctors
data.meta_description: Familiarize yourself with the licensed pediatric dentistry staff doctors at Red Rock Kids Dental in Las Vegas, led by Dr. Alice P. Chen.
data.text:
Dr. Charlene Mo

Dr. Charlene Mo was born and raised in Los Angeles and completed her Bachelor of Science in Psychobiology at UCLA. She graduated from Roseman University of Health Sciences for dental school and received her DMD (Doctor of Dental Medicine). She then went on to complete an additional two-year residency at UNLV for her specialty certificate in

pediatric dentistry.

Dr. Charlene strives to provide fun and comfortable dental experiences for your child and empower you to make the best decisions about your child’s oral health. She is dedicated to creating a bigger, brighter, and healthier smile for your child. When she’s not in the office, Dr. Charlene loves to play golf, travel with friends, and make her own fresh pasta!

Dr. Karen Kang

Dr. Karen is on a mission to create healthy smiles and ensure both patients and parents have positive experiences. Her gentle and conservative approach, combined with years of dental expertise guarantees exceptional care for your child.

Dr. Karen Kang’s birthplace in South Korea and upbringing in Georgia add a unique cultural perspective to her care. Driven by her calling to pediatric dentistry, she brings this diverse background and a wealth of experience to every patient in her care.

Dr. Karen Kang earned her Doctor of Dental Medicine degree from the Medical College of Georgia, laying the foundation for her dental expertise. Driven by her passion for pediatric dentistry, she went on to complete specialized training at Temple University Hospital, becoming proficient in treating diverse pediatric patients and sedation dentistry techniques. Dr. Karen is also a proud board-certified member of the American Board of Pediatric Dentistry.

Beyond her role as a dedicated pediatric dentist, Dr. Kang enjoys exploring her culinary talents, embarking on exciting travel adventures, and savoring precious moments with her cherished family.
